{"nodes": [{"id": "draft6_0_research_papers_phase6_readme", "label": "phase6/ README \u2014 noise-robust SCFF", "file_type": "document", "source_file": "draft6.0\\research\\papers\\phase6\\README.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "A Stage-1 extension pulled to the front of the queue: is the SCFF representation robust to noise, and if not, where does the fix have to live? Motivated by LP-FT \u2014 a frozen backbone caps the head's robustness, so if sensitivity originates in SCFF, no clever 20% GD can rescue it."}, {"id": "draft6_0_research_papers_phase6_two_noise_channels", "label": "Two noise channels: analog device noise vs continual/data noise", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "draft6.0\\research\\papers\\phase6\\README.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Door A: capacitor/op-amp/ADC device noise, directional and aligned with class axis, the residual mismatch surviving auto-zero. Door B: the model never sees a clean curated truth set \u2014 its entire world is noisy real-world samples arriving one at a time. Both reduce to the same geometric target (flatness) but attack through different doors."}, {"id": "draft6_0_research_papers_phase6_unifying_flatness_target", "label": "Unifying target: flatness, two levers for two channels", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "draft6.0\\research\\papers\\phase6\\README.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Input/tap/ADC channel: Bishop input-noise = Tikhonov penalty (inject input/tap noise at train time). Weight/charge channel: flat minima via SAM/S-SGD (inject symmetric weight noise). Data/label stream channel: noise-aware objective + replay hygiene. Attribution discipline: Bishop is input noise, NOT weight noise \u2014 don't conflate."}, {"id": "draft6_0_research_papers_phase6_arc_fork", "label": "The arc fork Phase 6 resolves (YES/NO branch)", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "draft6.0\\research\\papers\\phase6\\README.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "YES: the per-sample-norm objective can be made noise-aware, cheap brain stays cheap, GD namer builds on a hardened base. NO: structured directional noise destroys the class direction regardless, and the whole substrate-as-designed can't hold the representation \u2014 the arc reopens. Test now, cheaply, in numpy, before silicon."}], "edges": [{"source": "draft6_0_research_papers_phase6_readme", "target": "draft6_0_research_papers_phase6_two_noise_channels", "relation": "frames", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "draft6.0\\research\\papers\\phase6\\README.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "draft6_0_research_papers_phase6_readme", "target": "draft6_0_research_papers_phase6_unifying_flatness_target", "relation": "unifies_via", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "draft6.0\\research\\papers\\phase6\\README.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "draft6_0_research_papers_phase6_readme", "target": "draft6_0_research_papers_phase6_arc_fork", "relation": "poses", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "draft6.0\\research\\papers\\phase6\\README.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "draft6_0_research_papers_phase6_readme", "target": "draft6_0_research_papers_phase6_lp_ft", "relation": "cites", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "draft6.0\\research\\papers\\phase6\\README.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "draft6_0_research_papers_phase6_readme", "target": "draft6_0_research_papers_phase6_all_data_is_noise", "relation": "indexes", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0,